13 SECTION 3. NEW LAW A new section of law to be codified
14 in the Oklahoma Statutes as Section 121 of Title 25, unless there is
15 created a duplication in numbering, reads as follows:
16 A. A social media company shall not permit an Oklahoma user who
17 is a minor less than sixteen (16) years of age to be an account
18 holder on a social media company's social media platform.
19 B. A social media company shall not permit an Oklahoma user who
20 is a minor of sixteen (16) or seventeen (17) years of age to be an
21 account holder on the social media company's social media platform
22 unless the minor has the express consent of a parent or legal
23 guardian.
24
