1 C. 1. A social media company shall verify the age of an
2 account holder.
3 2. If an account holder is a minor of sixteen (16) or seventeen
4 (17) years of age, the social media company shall confirm that the
5 minor has consent under subsection B of this section to become a new
6 account holder at the time the Oklahoma user opens the account.
7 D. 1. A social media company may use a third-party vendor to
8 perform reasonable age verification before allowing access to the
9 social media company's social media platform.
10 2. Reasonable age verification methods under paragraph 1 of
11 this subsection include providing:
12 a. a digitized identification card, including a digital
13 copy of a driver license,
14 b. government-issued identification,
15 c. any commercially reasonable age verification method,
16 or
17 d. confirmation from a platform from which social media
18 applications are downloaded that the platform has
19 verified the age of the user.
